result.execSummary:
The defendant James R Kamke was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 2nd Degree Sexual Assault of Child, a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.02(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: If probation is revoked or will discharge with outstanding financial obligations due, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due.

Defendant shall obtain HSED/GED.
Defendant shall obtain/maintain full-time employment or school.
Defendant shall submit to random drug screens including blood, breath or urine.

Defendant shall have no contact with NAG or her family members.
Defendant shall have no unsupervised contact with females under the age of 18 years.
Defendant shall not view any sexually explicit materials.
Defendant shall not enter establishments where the primary purpose is the sale or service of alcohol.
Defendant shall not possess or consume any controlled substances without a valid prescription.

Defendant shall provide a DNA sample and pay the surcharge.
Defendant shall undergo sex offender treatment.
Defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety.
Per order of the Court, sex offender registration is not required.

timeConds.notes: Time shall be served with Huber privileges consistent with the rules of the jail while the inmate maintains a minimum security status. The defendant, at the discretion of the Sheriff, may perform community service work as an inmate worker in the county jail and shall earn statutory good time for same.

superMiscConds.notes:
Defendant shall have no contact with N.A.G., her family or her residence.
Defendant shall have no unsupervised contact with females under the age of 18 years.  
Defendant shall not possess or consume any controlled substances without a valid prescription.
Defendant shall not associate with known drug users or be present where drugs are illegally purchased, sold or consumed.

Defendant shall participate in all counseling and/or treatment programs directed by the probation agent.
Defendant shall participate in sex offender treatment and sex offender registration.
Defendant shall take medications as prescribed.
Defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety.

Any outstanding financial obligations shall be paid as a condition of extended supervision.
lf extended supervision is revoked and the defendant will have a mandatory release from prison, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due.
